Articles.Content:
Edited post, please use a paste site or code tags ([noparse]

[/noparse]) caitiemew, super long logs pasted directly to the forum are a bit of a bugbear.
I think I can guess your missing parts issue, I bet your R&D screen is blank as well, you say you used addons and it's likely you used something that changed your tech tree with module manager.
Search your persistent.sfs for "TechTreeUrl" and change the value from module manager to "GameData/Squad/Resources/TechTree.cfg", that should fix it.
If you're still getting lock-ups, post your output_log (it's in KSP_Data and don't forget code tags).

well, since having reinstalled, I have all the parts and everything, and this error report was from the last time trying to run it. Also I didn't even know about said tag, but I'll certainly keep it in mind. Going to try running KSP again, and just trying to build a simple spaceplane, to see if it still locks up or not, will post the results either way.
Great, and yeah it's not that well known a tag, there is a button for it in the advanced editor though, also if you are using -force-opengl try without it, it is not working properly on Win10.

Seems to be working okay now, I think what may have been a problem, is that when it was loaded up via steam, it didn't use the launcher, but when I used the launcher, I went to options and disabled 64bit. Seems to be running fine since doing that.

I hadn't tried to force opengl, hadn't gotten that far yet.

Edited August 3, 2015 by caitiemew
Glad it's working for you now, if you do get any more trouble let us know, we'll try to help
